Product: NRS Healthcare M15691 Portable Overbed/Chair Table - Tilting, Adjustable and Wheeled
Review:
Im finally organised! Wish I‚Äôd got this 6 weeks ago....

Working from home during Lockdown (office on the bed LOL) it‚Äôs taken me ages setting up / breaking down my kit everyday, but not anymore!

It only took a few minutes to assemble, without needing any tools. The A4 instruction sheet is in large readable text, using step-by-step notes & photos.

One niggle about the instruction sheet - the bars supporting the table top have 2 retractable buttons holding them in place, not one as shown in the photos & notes!

I set up my Surface Pro laptop, an external hard drive, desk fan, reading light AND I still have space on the table top to use my mouse!

Being right-handed, my laptop is on the left hand side of the table, with the fulcrum point (law of physics) furthest away - so you get ‚Äúbounce‚Äù when typing - not enough to be an issue, but when doing long reports or letters, it might make me move the laptop over to the right side / lessen the distance to the down supports = less bounce!

The surface is sealed / wipe clean (not sure why other reviews mention a papery surface?)

The table top is side-edged with a black plastic shielding which doesn‚Äôt sit very ‚Äòproud‚Äô of the surface - maybe 1mm or 2mm - meaning mouse control / typing is still comfortable while resting your arms across the edge.... but the ridge isn‚Äôt high enough to stop items sliding off, especially if you‚Äòre using the table top at a slightly tilted angle - perfect for my use, but might be an issue for people wanting the table top to retain items / stop pens rolling off!

Tilting the top to an angle takes a couple of seconds & fixes firmly in place - again perfect for my use (mouse control / typing / reading)

Still can‚Äôt believe the value for money on this purchase - sturdy, robust, easy to manoeuvre and a large working area!

Absolutely love it!!

Review: Purchased for a member of the family who had a seven weeks stay in hospital and now recovering at home.Excellent purchase which looks similar to the one in the hospital.  Used for meal times and also using for resting books and phone.  The tilting feature has not been used yet so can't comment on that.  Excellent portability and wheels run smoothly from bed to chair.  It also fits nicely around the bed and chair.Perfect size and not to small and not too big.  This is recommended

Product: NRS Healthcare M80282 Kura Care Easy Grip Children's Cutlery Set, Multi-Colour
Review:
Junior still can't hold a spoon at 2.5 years, has developmental delay and sensory issues amongst other things and always big issues around food generally. For some reason he uses finger and thumb to hold cutlery /really weak fist if we're lucky and ends up turning it upside down before it reaches his mouth (again for unknown reasons!) He also won't touch most food so we end up feeding him, but given his age he's been point blank refusing as he's craving control but just can't manage it. We've tried EVERYTHING...or so we thought!

The shape of this set has just meant he has managed to stab tomatoes and strawberries, scooped omelette and yoghurt and SOME MADE IT TO HIS MOUTH rather than his lap! We did iiiiiit!!!

Also arrived in a couple of days and the colours are appealing to children. The edges are curved so risk of injury is less, but the knife actually does cut and the fork is still pointed enough to actually get through food such as tomato skins, peppers etc.

We have had such stress around mealtimes recently and it sounds dramatic but it's honestly helped a situation that was starting to make the whole family miserable and dread mealtimes. Thank you so much!

Review: Before moving to Florida from NY Ik bought this as a safe measure, just in case... well the whole way there I was extremely worried, he started to stop eating and acting weird, lethargic, panting, no interest, stoped pooping and peeing. The minute we arrived to my new apartment, we dropped everything off, and rushed him to the vet. It was a very big vet bill, and he had to stay over night. But the vet said that if it weren‚Äôt for this he would have already been dead. I owe it to this company, it saved his life. Everyone rallied quickly after having this without any negative side effects. My vet recommended it. I keep it on hand in the freezer in case any foundlings come to the house. I think it's funny that the review asks you to rate the flavor, but the bearded dragon won't answer me when I ask him about that, so I just gave it 5/5. The cat begs for it, so that's a good sign. It smells like armpit, though.

Product: Oxbow Animal Health Critical Care, Herbivore, Apple-Banana Flavor, 141 Gram Bag
Review: My rabbit Chubbs had GI Stasis back in October and this helped bring him out of it. He ended up sick again with something else 3-4 weeks ago. The vet couldn‚Äôt figure out what was wrong. Still see a vet as medications can be required, but this will help with nutrition and getting water in them since you mix with water. I have a spare bag just in case our other rabbit ends up needing it. Chubbs did like the taste. He gobbled it up while he was sick last.

Review: I persevered with this for a couple of months but found it really tricky to use. I couldn‚Äôt think of anything to write without being repetitive. Doing a good deed every day is tricky when you work alone most of the time so I had to put down daily jobs such as cooking dinner for me and my husband or walking the dogs. After about two months of repetitive writing I felt that the diary had provided me with absolutely no benefit at all. I prefer taking a walk with my dogs or spending time outdoors in my garden when the weather is good. That had a far better effect on my mind and sense of well-being. Product: The 6-Minute Diary | Gratitude Journal for Men & Women, Mindfulness Journal | 6 Minutes a Day for more Self Care, Mental Health & Happiness
Review:
I bought this to go with a couple of books for my children (the 5 minute diary for the eldest and the 3 minute one for the younger child)... My initial objective was to get them to be grateful for their dinner... even if it's NOT chicken nuggets... be grateful you have food, you have warmth, you have comfort, even if the dinner had REAL chicken in it, as well as mushrooms!!! ... and that seemed to work, we got over that, not entirely of course, but a lesson has been learned (somewhat) in that department...
The unexpected by product of this experience however, is that THIS book grabbed my attention... it's not 'just' a gratitude journal which you write stuff down, it's the preamble, it's the all the information up front - the bit about why you're doing it in the first place...
That's what hooked me...
And then practicing the ritual with my daughters each day.
And at first, it was clutching at the obvious; grateful for food, water, clothes, warmth
But then something started to change, unexpectedly so... I started to dig deeper and feel more positive...
My gratitude now involves; realising my self worth and what I mean to my children, recognising what we have, not what we don't, grateful for opportunities and more meaningful, deeper reflection when it comes to positive affirmations....and one of my good deeds today, was simply 'Acceptance'... and 'Acceptance with grace'...
I love this book.
I have recommended and even bought copies for friends and colleagues...
I am more positive, more energised, more determined and dare I say happier in myself... I didn't even realise I needed changing, my days had been focused on other people and things and work and jobs which needed doing, that I forgot myself along the way. But I'm back now... and it feels great :)

Product: The 6-Minute Diary | Gratitude Journal for Men & Women, Mindfulness Journal | 6 Minutes a Day for more Self Care, Mental Health & Happiness
Review: I love this diary/journal. I used the first version for 6 months and have now started on the Pure edition. This takes your thinking to the next level. There are suggested guidelines, but really it's up to you to decide what you want to focus on, in terms of Gratitude in your day. In a busy world, where time is of the essence, to sit down in the morning with a cuppa and consider what/who you are greatful for is a positive way to start the day. Similarly to reflect in the evening brings everything together. I was reviewing my first journal and it brought back happy memories of the small things that made me smile, in a big life that sometimes doesn't. I've found this process invaluable for my postive mental health. Highly recommended.

Product: The 6-Minute Diary | Gratitude Journal for Men & Women, Mindfulness Journal | 6 Minutes a Day for more Self Care, Mental Health & Happiness
Review: I'm only 2 weeks into using this but the effect is startling. I found being prompted to think in this way very jarring at first. It's completely contrary to how my brain works, which is why I need it. It's very simple to do and not too full of the usual self help tropes that catch in my cynical throat. I wish I'd discovered this earlier, the effect was instant and is becoming stronger with practice. I haven't missed a day yet and it has never felt like a chore.

Product: The 6-Minute Diary | Gratitude Journal for Men & Women, Mindfulness Journal | 6 Minutes a Day for more Self Care, Mental Health & Happiness
Review: I came across this little gem by chance, I was just searching for a planner. What an amazing book! I have only completed about 5-6 days so far, but I am already feeling really inspired and motivated. The section at the beginning is a fantastic start to prepare you, then the free ebooks that you receive once started really help to keep you feeling positive and motivated to make those small changes that will add up to big changes overall. I will be recommending the 6 minute diary to everyone!

Product: The 6-Minute Diary | Gratitude Journal for Men & Women, Mindfulness Journal | 6 Minutes a Day for more Self Care, Mental Health & Happiness
Review: I was initially given this book for Christmas. Was a bit sceptical but have found it so helpful especially in the present climate of covid-19 that I have sent it as a gift to several friends. It was easy to get into the habit of filling it in morning and evening and I looked forward to the weekly questions which allowed me to delve a bit deeper. Review: I love this daily journal. I was nervous about getting something like this for myself because I‚Äôm not used to journaling everyday but I found the prompts short and easy to incorporate in my daily routine. It really does take 6 minutes each day (3 in the am, 3 in the pm). I do however worry that I will get tired of the same 6 daily propers after a few months, but overall I think they are great ways for me to express gratitude, start on a positive note, and mentally organize my day. My favorite things about the daily are the weekly prompts and the reading section at the beginning. The Diary starts with evidence based research that shows why adding this to your daily routine helps. I loved that it answered a lot of my questions and worries about being able to keep up with the journal and gave me helpful tips for starting new and healthier habits such as journaling. The weekly prompts also help break up the daily routine by fostering reflection. They change week to week which is really nice. I also like the weekly challenges - a great way to add some positivity or new things in your week. I highly recommend this diary. It‚Äôs also a great gift for someone who like journaling or is on a personal journey.

Review:
Having just completed using the 5 Minute Journal for the past six months, I was looking for an alternative to carry on this great practice I developed. I landed on this book, The 6 Minute Diary.

First, I will say that I am completely surprised that the authors were able to publish this book because of its similarities to the 5 Minute Journal. The introduction section is nearly identical, but it was a good refresher.

The differences: I absolutely love the monthly habit trackers. The 5 Minute Journal doesn‚Äôt have these and it‚Äôs a nice addition. Additionally, there is a space to capture weekly notes. I love having extra space to jot down highlights throughout the week.

This book was an easy transition from the 5 Minute Journal with a few extra bonuses.

These books have absolutely changed my life. My husband commented that I wake up in a better mood and I‚Äôve noticed I have developed a more positive and grateful outlook on life.

If you decide to purchase it, I hope it brings you as much joy as it does for me!

Review:
Grass cutting season has started again... which means allergy season for 2 of my Maltese.
Not even 6 hours after the grass being cut they had both started to scratch and chew their paws.

I have tried many many creams and spray over the years, including various (expensive) treatments from the vet and even the use of steroids for one of them as she had got so bad she was going bald with all her itching!

My male had managed to scratch a horrible sore onto his stomach area, I had tried treating it with another well- known dog anti itch brand for several days with no luck what so ever and figured it was going to have to be another vet trip before the cut turned into a full-blown wound and would get infected. I had seen this spray advertised several times but to be honest, I just assumed it would be the same as all the others I already have sitting in the cupboard which didn't work for us. However, when telling a friend I was going to have to take him back to the vet she recommended trying Leucillin Antiseptic Skin Care Spray and told me her vet uses it and that she had had great results too so decided it was worth a go.

Item arrived really quickly and spraying it onto the cut didn't seem to bother him at all. Within a day the sore had already started to look better. Even better my dog was no longer scratching at the area or trying to constantly lick it. Have used the spray for 3 days (twice a day although it does recommend 3 times) and today the area has completely healed and no longer red or sore. My other Maltese hasn't been as bad (so far) this year however she has been chewing at her paws a bit. I have given her feet a quick spray once a day and that alone seems to be enough to stop her biting and causing more harm.

Am truly amazed by how well it has worked, although have to say I'm a little annoyed I didn't purchase it sooner as I would have saved the dogs many summers of itching misery and myself many large vet bills!

Product: The 6-Minute Diary Pure | Gratitude Journal, Mindfulness Journal for Men & Women | 6 Minutes a Day for more Mental Health, Happiness & Self Care
Review: I absolutely love this product.  I started with the Six Minute Diary but was rather half-hearted about it - thinking it couldn't possibly be just six minutes a day... but it arrived and I filled it in that day ... and the next day... and the next day...I loved the daily quotes/affirmations;  I loved the fact that the statements/questions are simple and straightforward and didn't make it feel like an exam or that there was a "wrong answer".  I just love it.So much that as I filled it in one day.. then the next... then the next... I came to the end of it.  I was delighted and disappointed all at the same time... so I immediately ordered the Six Minute Diary Plus... and am very much looking to not only continuing my morning and evening "journalling" (which has improved my focus on my life, my goals, what I will accept and what is unacceptable to me) and I have high hopes that "Plus" will allow me to continue to start and end each day in a positive, productive, pro-active mindset - which has had a massive beneficial impact on so many other aspects of my life.I'm going to end here because I know I'm beginning to sound evangelical about it... but I really can't recommend it highly enough.  Buy it and tell yourself "I'll give it my best shot for a week"... don't look at the whole book and think I'll never get to the end... just tell yourself "seven days".  That's what I did... but the first seven days were followed by the second seven days.. then the third ... and the fourth... and ... on those days where I couldn't fill it in first thing (with a cup of coffee in bed) ... I missed it.  My day didn't "start right"... and on those rare occasions where I couldn't end my day positively reflecting on all the good things that had happened... I went to sleep with my heart that little bit less content .. and I couldn't hear my soul singing the lullaby that the diary created every evening.Buy it.  Try it.  I hope, like me, you'll love it.

Product: The 6-Minute Diary Pure | Gratitude Journal, Mindfulness Journal for Men & Women | 6 Minutes a Day for more Mental Health, Happiness & Self Care
Review:
I bought this to go with a couple of books for my children (the 5 minute diary for the eldest and the 3 minute one for the younger child)... My initial objective was to get them to be grateful for their dinner... even if it's NOT chicken nuggets... be grateful you have food, you have warmth, you have comfort, even if the dinner had REAL chicken in it, as well as mushrooms!!! ... and that seemed to work, we got over that, not entirely of course, but a lesson has been learned (somewhat) in that department...
The unexpected by product of this experience however, is that THIS book grabbed my attention... it's not 'just' a gratitude journal which you write stuff down, it's the preamble, it's the all the information up front - the bit about why you're doing it in the first place...
That's what hooked me...
And then practicing the ritual with my daughters each day.
And at first, it was clutching at the obvious; grateful for food, water, clothes, warmth
But then something started to change, unexpectedly so... I started to dig deeper and feel more positive...
My gratitude now involves; realising my self worth and what I mean to my children, recognising what we have, not what we don't, grateful for opportunities and more meaningful, deeper reflection when it comes to positive affirmations....and one of my good deeds today, was simply 'Acceptance'... and 'Acceptance with grace'...
I love this book.
I have recommended and even bought copies for friends and colleagues...
I am more positive, more energised, more determined and dare I say happier in myself... I didn't even realise I needed changing, my days had been focused on other people and things and work and jobs which needed doing, that I forgot myself along the way. But I'm back now... and it feels great :)

Product: The 6-Minute Diary Pure | Gratitude Journal, Mindfulness Journal for Men & Women | 6 Minutes a Day for more Mental Health, Happiness & Self Care
Review: I got a lot out of the first volume of The 6-Minute Diary.  It helped me, a natural pessimist, to take stock of and appreciate the good things in life just by asking me a few simple (and yes, repetitive) questions every single day, with a weekly set of deeper questions that ultimately helped me think about what was important in life to me.  This second volume is useful for keeping that positivity and gratitude going. I gave it only 4 stars because the weekly reflection, which I used to find sometimes challenging but definitely enlightening, has been replaced by a 'lighter' version, although I can see that it is still useful. Overall I have found that creating the habit of thinking about the positives in life, however small, has been really beneficial for me.

Product: Boxclever Press Luxury A5 Diary Cover. Textured Cover with Zip for A5 Diaries & Journals. Untitled Diary Covers for Nurses, Health Care Professionals, Students or Home Use. (Seaspray)
Review: Solid with stiff board inside and the faux leather material appears quite thick. The general construction and sewing appears very good. However the item is lacking in finesse. Velcro on small pocket not aligned, so does not hold closed. However this is academic since the  pocket is not of any use.! More important, the zip, although solid, is very rough making it-for me- unusable; it jams sometimes unless I am very careful and deliberate. It reminds me of zips from 40 years ago. There is binding next to the zip. Rather than using one piece, the manufacturers have continued with a join which is unsightly and has a black mark on it. Overall the fit is tight even with a 12 cm thick A5 notebook. with a 20 mm spiral wire spine, placed inside. Personally I would have prefered if it were 5-10 mm thicker.  I am disappointed, mainly because of the zip.

Review:
In the 1860's this soap was a by-product of the distillation of coal to make coke; the liquid was made into Wrights¬†antiseptic soap for the treatment of skin diseases.

These days the use of coal tar in non-prescription products has been banned, and so the Wrights traditional (or not so traditional) soap you can buy only has a coal tar fragrance.¬†

Still, it's a good old fashioned soap with the same smell, just without¬†the coal tar!

Product: Wright's Traditional Coal Tar Soap 002629, 500 gram, Pack of 4
Review:
I procured a pack of these heading into the CV19 era as a backup, thinking that there would come a time when, bereft of all liquid soap, all fragrant latherings, we would be forced to turn native, to return to the scent of coal tar soap....

I had to turn to it sooner than I ever expected..... The increased washing with the Blue scented liquid soap did no favours to my delicate digits. Dryness and itchiness setting in irrespective of how much Scandinavian hand cream I applied twixt scrubbing.

I started on the Wright's and immediately knew the Right choice had been made...

I was catapulted back to childhood days....that smell...it lingers....and I remember

No more dryness, no more itchy prickly pinkies....just a dab of hand cream and life is good...

However......the department of infernal affairs, (she who must be listened to..)..despises the smell....but I've been allowed to keep my bar of Wright's in a sealed box, by the sink. ...for now...

Product: The 6-Minute Diary | Gratitude Journal for Men & Women, Mindfulness Journal | 6 Minutes a Day for more Self Care, Mental Health & Happiness
Review:
I bought this to go with a couple of books for my children (the 5 minute diary for the eldest and the 3 minute one for the younger child)... My initial objective was to get them to be grateful for their dinner... even if it's NOT chicken nuggets... be grateful you have food, you have warmth, you have comfort, even if the dinner had REAL chicken in it, as well as mushrooms!!! ... and that seemed to work, we got over that, not entirely of course, but a lesson has been learned (somewhat) in that department...
The unexpected by product of this experience however, is that THIS book grabbed my attention... it's not 'just' a gratitude journal which you write stuff down, it's the preamble, it's the all the information up front - the bit about why you're doing it in the first place...
That's what hooked me...
And then practicing the ritual with my daughters each day.
And at first, it was clutching at the obvious; grateful for food, water, clothes, warmth
But then something started to change, unexpectedly so... I started to dig deeper and feel more positive...
My gratitude now involves; realising my self worth and what I mean to my children, recognising what we have, not what we don't, grateful for opportunities and more meaningful, deeper reflection when it comes to positive affirmations....and one of my good deeds today, was simply 'Acceptance'... and 'Acceptance with grace'...
I love this book.
I have recommended and even bought copies for friends and colleagues...
I am more positive, more energised, more determined and dare I say happier in myself... I didn't even realise I needed changing, my days had been focused on other people and things and work and jobs which needed doing, that I forgot myself along the way. But I'm back now... and it feels great :)

Product: The 6-Minute Diary | Gratitude Journal for Men & Women, Mindfulness Journal | 6 Minutes a Day for more Self Care, Mental Health & Happiness
Review: I love this diary/journal. I used the first version for 6 months and have now started on the Pure edition. This takes your thinking to the next level. There are suggested guidelines, but really it's up to you to decide what you want to focus on, in terms of Gratitude in your day. In a busy world, where time is of the essence, to sit down in the morning with a cuppa and consider what/who you are greatful for is a positive way to start the day. Similarly to reflect in the evening brings everything together. I was reviewing my first journal and it brought back happy memories of the small things that made me smile, in a big life that sometimes doesn't. I've found this process invaluable for my postive mental health. Highly recommended.

Product: The 6-Minute Diary | Gratitude Journal for Men & Women, Mindfulness Journal | 6 Minutes a Day for more Self Care, Mental Health & Happiness

I wish I'd discovered this earlier, the effect was instant and is becoming stronger with practice. I haven't missed a day yet and it has never felt like a chore.

Review:
Having just completed using the 5 Minute Journal for the past six months, I was looking for an alternative to carry on this great practice I developed. I landed on this book, The 6 Minute Diary.

First, I will say that I am completely surprised that the authors were able to publish this book because of its similarities to the 5 Minute Journal. The introduction section is nearly identical, but it was a good refresher.

The differences: I absolutely love the monthly habit trackers. The 5 Minute Journal doesn‚Äôt have these and it‚Äôs a nice addition. Additionally, there is a space to capture weekly notes. I love having extra space to jot down highlights throughout the week.

This book was an easy transition from the 5 Minute Journal with a few extra bonuses.

These books have absolutely changed my life. My husband commented that I wake up in a better mood and I‚Äôve noticed I have developed a more positive and grateful outlook on life.

If you decide to purchase it, I hope it brings you as much joy as it does for me!

Product: The 6-Minute Diary | Gratitude Journal for Men & Women, Mindfulness Journal | 6 Minutes a Day for more Self Care, Mental Health & Happiness
Review: I love this daily journal. I was nervous about getting something like this for myself because I‚Äôm not used to journaling everyday but I found the prompts short and easy to incorporate in my daily routine. It really does take 6 minutes each day (3 in the am, 3 in the pm). I do however worry that I will get tired of the same 6 daily propers after a few months, but overall I think they are great ways for me to express gratitude, start on a positive note, and mentally organize my day. My favorite things about the daily are the weekly prompts and the reading section at the beginning. The Diary starts with evidence based research that shows why adding this to your daily routine helps. I loved that it answered a lot of my questions and worries about being able to keep up with the journal and gave me helpful tips for starting new and healthier habits such as journaling. The weekly prompts also help break up the daily routine by fostering reflection. They change week to week which is really nice. I also like the weekly challenges - a great way to add some positivity or new things in your week. I highly recommend this diary. It‚Äôs also a great gift for someone who like journaling or is on a personal journey.

Product: NRS Healthcare M15691 Portable Overbed/Chair Table - Tilting, Adjustable and Wheeled
Review:
Im finally organised! Wish I‚Äôd got this 6 weeks ago....

Working from home during Lockdown (office on the bed LOL) it‚Äôs taken me ages setting up / breaking down my kit everyday, but not anymore!

It only took a few minutes to assemble, without needing any tools. The A4 instruction sheet is in large readable text, using step-by-step notes & photos.

One niggle about the instruction sheet - the bars supporting the table top have 2 retractable buttons holding them in place, not one as shown in the photos & notes!

I set up my Surface Pro laptop, an external hard drive, desk fan, reading light AND I still have space on the table top to use my mouse!

Being right-handed, my laptop is on the left hand side of the table, with the fulcrum point (law of physics) furthest away - so you get ‚Äúbounce‚Äù when typing - not enough to be an issue, but when doing long reports or letters, it might make me move the laptop over to the right side / lessen the distance to the down supports = less bounce!

The surface is sealed / wipe clean (not sure why other reviews mention a papery surface?)

The table top is side-edged with a black plastic shielding which doesn‚Äôt sit very ‚Äòproud‚Äô of the surface - maybe 1mm or 2mm - meaning mouse control / typing is still comfortable while resting your arms across the edge.... but the ridge isn‚Äôt high enough to stop items sliding off, especially if you‚Äòre using the table top at a slightly tilted angle - perfect for my use, but might be an issue for people wanting the table top to retain items / stop pens rolling off!

Tilting the top to an angle takes a couple of seconds & fixes firmly in place - again perfect for my use (mouse control / typing / reading)

Still can‚Äôt believe the value for money on this purchase - sturdy, robust, easy to manoeuvre and a large working area!

Absolutely love it!!

Product: Tommee Tippee Healthcare Kit for Baby, Black, 9 Count
Review: Awful quality, there's nothing in this set that can actually be used. I had to buy every single item separately. I'll give you a few reasons for not buying this product. 1. The nail clip blade is extremely sharp and presents some irregularities. I've tried to cut my newborn nails and just by touching it cut my baby's skin, haven't even pressed on it. Checking it on with my finger I have realised it's too sharp. 2. Baby brush and comb... seriously? Those are not suitable for delicate baby skin, the bristles are too strong. 3. Digital thermometer - that should be posed under baby's arm or mouth to give the temperature... that's a joke. First of all, baby is wriggling too much and it's impossible to keep the thermometer in position under arm for around 1 minute. Secondly, you can't make the baby keep the mouth shut for a better temperature measurement... otherwise, I've tested on my own mouth and was giving a result of 34deg Celsius which is impossible. 4. Nose cleaner - there are better products out there that can actually do the job. 5. Nail file - single use. 6. Teeth brush for newborn and baby? The brush has plastic bristles which are not suitable for baby that can chew and swallow. Unfortunately, I cannot return it as I bought this product long time in advance before the baby was born. But please make yourself a favour and avoid buying this.

Product: Hibiscrub Health Care, 500ml
Review:
Thankfully, I thought about this product as soon as the virus that we all want to be eradicated raised its head. Well, this was probably my best purchase for sanitising my hands. This gel is antiseptic and given it is used before conducting surgery and minor operations, I think it's effectiveness is unquestionable.

I am very thorough when washing my hands and usually rub the gel into my hands for around 3 minutes, with close attention to all areas and under the nails. However, the peace of mind afterwards is fantastic, as even though I take a sanitizer with me too, you feel "bulletproof" knowing this product has a residual effect for up to 6 hours!

The smell is pleasant and I have not had any allergic reaction despite having sensitive skin. However, this handwash is not cheap but you get what you pay for, so the peace of mind is worth every penny!!!

Product: The 6-Minute Diary | Gratitude Journal for Men & Women, Mindfulness Journal | 6 Minutes a Day for more Self Care, Mental Health & Happiness
Review:
Having just completed using the 5 Minute Journal for the past six months, I was looking for an alternative to carry on this great practice I developed. I landed on this book, The 6 Minute Diary.

First, I will say that I am completely surprised that the authors were able to publish this book because of its similarities to the 5 Minute Journal. The introduction section is nearly identical, but it was a good refresher.

The differences: I absolutely love the monthly habit trackers. The 5 Minute Journal doesn‚Äôt have these and it‚Äôs a nice addition. Additionally, there is a space to capture weekly notes. I love having extra space to jot down highlights throughout the week.

This book was an easy transition from the 5 Minute Journal with a few extra bonuses.

These books have absolutely changed my life. My husband commented that I wake up in a better mood and I‚Äôve noticed I have developed a more positive and grateful outlook on life.

If you decide to purchase it, I hope it brings you as much joy as it does for me!

Product: The 6-Minute Diary | Gratitude Journal for Men & Women, Mindfulness Journal | 6 Minutes a Day for more Self Care, Mental Health & Happiness
Review: I love this daily journal. I was nervous about getting something like this for myself because I‚Äôm not used to journaling everyday but I found the prompts short and easy to incorporate in my daily routine. It really does take 6 minutes each day (3 in the am, 3 in the pm). I do however worry that I will get tired of the same 6 daily propers after a few months, but overall I think they are great ways for me to express gratitude, start on a positive note, and mentally organize my day. My favorite things about the daily are the weekly prompts and the reading section at the beginning. The Diary starts with evidence based research that shows why adding this to your daily routine helps. I loved that it answered a lot of my questions and worries about being able to keep up with the journal and gave me helpful tips for starting new and healthier habits such as journaling. The weekly prompts also help break up the daily routine by fostering reflection. They change week to week which is really nice. I also like the weekly challenges - a great way to add some positivity or new things in your week. I highly recommend this diary. It‚Äôs also a great gift for someone who like journaling or is on a personal journey.

Product: NRS Healthcare M15691 Portable Overbed/Chair Table - Tilting, Adjustable and Wheeled
Review:
Im finally organised! Wish I‚Äôd got this 6 weeks ago....

Working from home during Lockdown (office on the bed LOL) it‚Äôs taken me ages setting up / breaking down my kit everyday, but not anymore!

It only took a few minutes to assemble, without needing any tools. The A4 instruction sheet is in large readable text, using step-by-step notes & photos.

One niggle about the instruction sheet - the bars supporting the table top have 2 retractable buttons holding them in place, not one as shown in the photos & notes!

I set up my Surface Pro laptop, an external hard drive, desk fan, reading light AND I still have space on the table top to use my mouse!

Being right-handed, my laptop is on the left hand side of the table, with the fulcrum point (law of physics) furthest away - so you get ‚Äúbounce‚Äù when typing - not enough to be an issue, but when doing long reports or letters, it might make me move the laptop over to the right side / lessen the distance to the down supports = less bounce!

The surface is sealed / wipe clean (not sure why other reviews mention a papery surface?)

The table top is side-edged with a black plastic shielding which doesn‚Äôt sit very ‚Äòproud‚Äô of the surface - maybe 1mm or 2mm - meaning mouse control / typing is still comfortable while resting your arms across the edge.... but the ridge isn‚Äôt high enough to stop items sliding off, especially if you‚Äòre using the table top at a slightly tilted angle - perfect for my use, but might be an issue for people wanting the table top to retain items / stop pens rolling off!

Tilting the top to an angle takes a couple of seconds & fixes firmly in place - again perfect for my use (mouse control / typing / reading)

Still can‚Äôt believe the value for money on this purchase - sturdy, robust, easy to manoeuvre and a large working area!

Absolutely love it!!

Product: NRS Healthcare M15691 Portable Overbed/Chair Table - Tilting, Adjustable and Wheeled
Review:
Im finally organised! Wish I‚Äôd got this 6 weeks ago....

Working from home during Lockdown (office on the bed LOL) it‚Äôs taken me ages setting up / breaking down my kit everyday, but not anymore!

It only took a few minutes to assemble, without needing any tools. The A4 instruction sheet is in large readable text, using step-by-step notes & photos.

One niggle about the instruction sheet - the bars supporting the table top have 2 retractable buttons holding them in place, not one as shown in the photos & notes!

I set up my Surface Pro laptop, an external hard drive, desk fan, reading light AND I still have space on the table top to use my mouse!

Being right-handed, my laptop is on the left hand side of the table, with the fulcrum point (law of physics) furthest away - so you get ‚Äúbounce‚Äù when typing - not enough to be an issue, but when doing long reports or letters, it might make me move the laptop over to the right side / lessen the distance to the down supports = less bounce!

The surface is sealed / wipe clean (not sure why other reviews mention a papery surface?)

The table top is side-edged with a black plastic shielding which doesn‚Äôt sit very ‚Äòproud‚Äô of the surface - maybe 1mm or 2mm - meaning mouse control / typing is still comfortable while resting your arms across the edge.... but the ridge isn‚Äôt high enough to stop items sliding off, especially if you‚Äòre using the table top at a slightly tilted angle - perfect for my use, but might be an issue for people wanting the table top to retain items / stop pens rolling off!

Tilting the top to an angle takes a couple of seconds & fixes firmly in place - again perfect for my use (mouse control / typing / reading)

Still can‚Äôt believe the value for money on this purchase - sturdy, robust, easy to manoeuvre and a large working area!

Absolutely love it!!

Review: After reading all the negative reviews (running into thousands) I was a bit dubious about using one of these vouchers but with the current Corona Virus situation going on around the world and the normal post being short of workers and basically in chaos, I despaired of getting a gift or even a card to the recipient on time.Anyway, I bit the bullet and risked potentially wasting ¬£25.  I needn't have worried.  My funny singing dogs gift voucher arrived on time.  How much on time, I'm not sure because the recipient couldn't find it and nearly ended up deleting it as it had gone into his spam folder.  He thought it was a scam and almost deleted it when he discovered it two days after I'd sent it!  It wasn't until I asked if he'd received it that he told me 'no' and I urged him to check his spam & trash folders, where it was discovered quietly lurking!I received an email as soon as I purchased it saying it had been sent and then another two days later saying it had been received.  Perhaps it only registers as being received once it has been put into the Gift Card section of the recipient's Amazon account.  Anyway, do send it a day or two before the occasion if you want the person to receive it on time because there does seem to be a bit of a longer delay than the fours hours stated in the terms and conditions.I'm definitely going to do this again though as I have another birthday coming up soon and the Covid thing isn't going to go away overnight.  I opted for an all-singing, all-dancing version - there are loads to choose from and they are are hilarious and don't cost any more than the boring ones with the plain Amazon logo.  I sent mine from my PC to an email address so that I wouldn't incur any extra charges but, if sent from a mobile phone, your service provider may charge you extra.

Product: Eye Complex 7: Lutein, Meso-Zeaxanthin, Zeaxanthin, NZ Blackcurrant, Bilberry, Goji & Eyebright ‚Äì 4 Month Supply ‚Äì UK Manufactured (120 Capsule Pouch)
Review: I now use a few different products from Time Health. The product seems to be of an excellent quality, and I'm especially appreciative to find natural, GMO free products made by a reliable company based in the UK.I had a high pressure read which scared me, so I began taking this. (I've also been doing some Chinese acupressure exercises to help things along.) My pressure levels decreased dramatically and my eye specialist approved of this supplement when I showed it to him. Product: Eye Complex 7: Lutein, Meso-Zeaxanthin, Zeaxanthin, NZ Blackcurrant, Bilberry, Goji & Eyebright ‚Äì 4 Month Supply ‚Äì UK Manufactured (120 Capsule Pouch)
Review:
I have diabetes, and eye problems with the diabetes. I didn't want my eyes to get worse.
So I researched and came across this product.

I have been taking it for about 6 months now.

I won't be seeing my eye specialist for another 6 months, so I will find out then what difference there is in my sight and eye tests by taking these for a year will have made.

However, in the meantime I have definitely noticed a few things:

1. I have had very dry eyes for a few decades now. I have Sjogrens Syndrome. Even eyedrops didn't work well, no matter how many I used, or what make I used. These capsules have improved my dry eyes a lot, to the extent that I can feel the benefit now when I use eyedrops. I still have dry eyes, but they are made comfortable now with eyedrops. Before taking these capsules my eyes were agonisingly dry and stuck together at night and felt like sandpaper rubbing together. But those horrible sensations have now gone. This is after 6 months of taking these capsules.

2. I was having difficulty with driving this time of year when the early morning and later afternoon sun is low in the sky. This sun blinded me. In the end I avoided those times of day this time of year.
Not any more. I was driving into blinding early morning sun, for an important appointment. I was going to go a different route when I suddenly realised I wasn't being blinded by this sun. . It was still very bright with those rays, but I wasn't being blinded by it. I have been out more days with this low sun, and my eyes are fine with it now.

3. Another thing, my night time vision has improved as well. I had stopped driving at night. But I found myself driving back, the other day, in the dark because everything over ran. Then I realised the oncoming headlights were not blinding me any more.

4. I also had found tunnels hard to drive through because I couldn't see well in them. So I would take a very long route to avoid river tunnels. But I found myself driving through a tunnel because I couldn't face the long route that day. Suddenly I realised (it was the same tunnel as previously), that the light didn't seem dim any more. Also in my back garden (I watch the stars in the night sky), I found that I could see in the dark much better.

So with taking these eye capsules for the last 6 months, I have noticed an improvement in the 4 things above.

I will continue to take these capsules always.

If, after research you decide these capsules could help, then I would say give them a go. It has taken me 6 months taking them daily that has got me to this point of improvement.

When I see my eye specialist next, I will come back and report what my eye specialist says. He said that some things would get worse in my eyes, that it was a natural progression. I am hoping that in 6 months time that my eyes will be no worse than when he tested them 6 months ago. That is my hope.

*****

UPDATE August 2021
I said I would come back when I had seen the specialist again. But Covid-19 and lockdowns got in the way, and the eye hospital was not seeing patients.

I continued taking these capsules and recently I saw my hospital eye specialist again (they were seeing patients again). My eyes are continuing to do well. They are not getting worse like the specialist said they would. My specialist is pleased with my progress.

I am very pleased with these capsules.

Also because of Covid-19 and the lockdown, the NHS retinopathy team in Wales were not monitoring patients. I should have had their eye checks because of my diabetes but they were not doing them. However, recently, just before my hospital eye appointment my opticians offered a similar test to check my eyes. I decided to pay for it. My optician showed me the results, and he said to carry on whatever I was doing because it was working for my eyes. My eyes were improved and I had stopped the natural progression my hospital specialist said was inevitable.

I shall continue with these capsules.

Thank you
gennepher

Product: Tommee Tippee Healthcare Kit for Baby, Black, 9 Count
Review: Awful quality, there's nothing in this set that can actually be used. I had to buy every single item separately. I'll give you a few reasons for not buying this product. 1. The nail clip blade is extremely sharp and presents some irregularities. I've tried to cut my newborn nails and just by touching it cut my baby's skin, haven't even pressed on it. Checking it on with my finger I have realised it's too sharp. 2. Baby brush and comb... seriously? Those are not suitable for delicate baby skin, the bristles are too strong. 3. Digital thermometer - that should be posed under baby's arm or mouth to give the temperature... that's a joke. First of all, baby is wriggling too much and it's impossible to keep the thermometer in position under arm for around 1 minute. Secondly, you can't make the baby keep the mouth shut for a better temperature measurement... otherwise, I've tested on my own mouth and was giving a result of 34deg Celsius which is impossible. 4. Nose cleaner - there are better products out there that can actually do the job. 5. Nail file - single use. 6. Teeth brush for newborn and baby? The brush has plastic bristles which are not suitable for baby that can chew and swallow. Unfortunately, I cannot return it as I bought this product long time in advance before the baby was born. But please make yourself a favour and avoid buying this.

Product: Leucillin Natural Antiseptic Spray | Antibacterial, Antifungal & Antiviral | for Dogs, Cats and All Animals | for Itchy Skin, Minor-wound Care and All Skin Care Health | 250ml
Review:
Grass cutting season has started again... which means allergy season for 2 of my Maltese.
Not even 6 hours after the grass being cut they had both started to scratch and chew their paws.

I have tried many many creams and spray over the years, including various (expensive) treatments from the vet and even the use of steroids for one of them as she had got so bad she was going bald with all her itching!

My male had managed to scratch a horrible sore onto his stomach area, I had tried treating it with another well- known dog anti itch brand for several days with no luck what so ever and figured it was going to have to be another vet trip before the cut turned into a full-blown wound and would get infected. I had seen this spray advertised several times but to be honest, I just assumed it would be the same as all the others I already have sitting in the cupboard which didn't work for us. However, when telling a friend I was going to have to take him back to the vet she recommended trying Leucillin Antiseptic Skin Care Spray and told me her vet uses it and that she had had great results too so decided it was worth a go.

Item arrived really quickly and spraying it onto the cut didn't seem to bother him at all. Within a day the sore had already started to look better. Even better my dog was no longer scratching at the area or trying to constantly lick it. Have used the spray for 3 days (twice a day although it does recommend 3 times) and today the area has completely healed and no longer red or sore. My other Maltese hasn't been as bad (so far) this year however she has been chewing at her paws a bit. I have given her feet a quick spray once a day and that alone seems to be enough to stop her biting and causing more harm.

Am truly amazed by how well it has worked, although have to say I'm a little annoyed I didn't purchase it sooner as I would have saved the dogs many summers of itching misery and myself many large vet bills!

Product: The 6-Minute Diary Pure | Gratitude Journal, Mindfulness Journal for Men & Women | 6 Minutes a Day for more Mental Health, Happiness & Self Care
Review:
I bought this to go with a couple of books for my children (the 5 minute diary for the eldest and the 3 minute one for the younger child)... My initial objective was to get them to be grateful for their dinner... even if it's NOT chicken nuggets... be grateful you have food, you have warmth, you have comfort, even if the dinner had REAL chicken in it, as well as mushrooms!!! ... and that seemed to work, we got over that, not entirely of course, but a lesson has been learned (somewhat) in that department...
The unexpected by product of this experience however, is that THIS book grabbed my attention... it's not 'just' a gratitude journal which you write stuff down, it's the preamble, it's the all the information up front - the bit about why you're doing it in the first place...
That's what hooked me...
And then practicing the ritual with my daughters each day.
And at first, it was clutching at the obvious; grateful for food, water, clothes, warmth
But then something started to change, unexpectedly so... I started to dig deeper and feel more positive...
My gratitude now involves; realising my self worth and what I mean to my children, recognising what we have, not what we don't, grateful for opportunities and more meaningful, deeper reflection when it comes to positive affirmations....and one of my good deeds today, was simply 'Acceptance'... and 'Acceptance with grace'...
I love this book.
I have recommended and even bought copies for friends and colleagues...
I am more positive, more energised, more determined and dare I say happier in myself... I didn't even realise I needed changing, my days had been focused on other people and things and work and jobs which needed doing, that I forgot myself along the way. But I'm back now... and it feels great :)

Product: The 6-Minute Diary Pure | Gratitude Journal, Mindfulness Journal for Men & Women | 6 Minutes a Day for more Mental Health, Happiness & Self Care
Review: I absolutely love this product.  I started with the Six Minute Diary but was rather half-hearted about it - thinking it couldn't possibly be just six minutes a day... but it arrived and I filled it in that day ... and the next day... and the next day...I loved the daily quotes/affirmations;  I loved the fact that the statements/questions are simple and straightforward and didn't make it feel like an exam or that there was a "wrong answer".  I just love it.So much that as I filled it in one day.. then the next... then the next... I came to the end of it.  I was delighted and disappointed all at the same time... so I immediately ordered the Six Minute Diary Plus... and am very much looking to not only continuing my morning and evening "journalling" (which has improved my focus on my life, my goals, what I will accept and what is unacceptable to me) and I have high hopes that "Plus" will allow me to continue to start and end each day in a positive, productive, pro-active mindset - which has had a massive beneficial impact on so many other aspects of my life.I'm going to end here because I know I'm beginning to sound evangelical about it... but I really can't recommend it highly enough.  Buy it and tell yourself "I'll give it my best shot for a week"... don't look at the whole book and think I'll never get to the end... just tell yourself "seven days".  That's what I did... but the first seven days were followed by the second seven days.. then the third ... and the fourth... and ... on those days where I couldn't fill it in first thing (with a cup of coffee in bed) ... I missed it.  My day didn't "start right"... and on those rare occasions where I couldn't end my day positively reflecting on all the good things that had happened... I went to sleep with my heart that little bit less content .. and I couldn't hear my soul singing the lullaby that the diary created every evening.Buy it.  Try it.  I hope, like me, you'll love it.

This gel is antiseptic and given it is used before conducting surgery and minor operations, I think it's effectiveness is unquestionable.

I am very thorough when washing my hands and usually rub the gel into my hands for around 3 minutes, with close attention to all areas and under the nails. However, the peace of mind afterwards is fantastic, as even though I take a sanitizer with me too, you feel "bulletproof" knowing this product has a residual effect for up to 6 hours!

The smell is pleasant and I have not had any allergic reaction despite having sensitive skin. However, this handwash is not cheap but you get what you pay for, so the peace of mind is worth every penny!!!

Product: Wright's Traditional Coal Tar Soap 002629, 500 gram, Pack of 4
Review: old fashioned soap how it used to be when your dad came home from work smelling and your mum complaining,shouting one word bath,anyway thats my memory of the 70s.in those days they used have just bars of soap,e.g.coal tar soap and thats how you got yourself clean,none of that fancy shower gel.still gets the muck off.still kills bacteria still smells like coal tar soap some things stay the same,Im am glad of that.paul

Product: Wright's Traditional Coal Tar Soap 002629, 500 gram, Pack of 4
Review: This is not traditional coal/tar soap. that joy was taken away by the EU that stated it was for prescription items only.This like many soaps contain animal fat taken from slaughted sheep/cattle.

Product: Wright's Traditional Coal Tar Soap 002629, 500 gram, Pack of 4
Review: Smells a little odd, but is helping my Psoriasis calm down a bit.Personally have no issues with the scent, it's an honest clean smell without the extra ingredients needed to make it flowery.

Product: Wright's Traditional Coal Tar Soap 002629, 500 gram, Pack of 4
Review: Am now 82 years old and can still remember it always being in our household from when I was around 5. Quality and smell has never changed which makes it useful for checking tinies hands after Bathrom use!  Bit too strong for me these days but makes me feel safe in these troubled times.

Product: Wright's Traditional Coal Tar Soap 002629, 500 gram, Pack of 4
Review: I've suffered the plight of bad eczema on my hands since birth (now 31) Been searching for a soap that doesn't dry out my hands and make them crack for years. This unfortunately wasn't the answer for me. Leaves my hands dryer than using conventional soaps. Thought it was working at first and then my hands ended up in a terrible state. May work for some but for bad Eczema I wouldn't recommend.Found a soap called Cetaphil, Seems to be working so far, It's expensive but it works. By I mean it works I mean it will not dry your skin, Not a cure. It will just allow you to wash your hands without a breakout, I'd recommend still sticking to your medication. Skin clear for 3 weeks.

Review:
In the 1860's this soap was a by-product of the distillation of coal to make coke; the liquid was made into Wrights¬†antiseptic soap for the treatment of skin diseases.

These days the use of coal tar in non-prescription products has been banned, and so the Wrights traditional (or not so traditional) soap you can buy only has a coal tar fragrance.¬†

Still, it's a good old fashioned soap with the same smell, just without¬†the coal tar!

Product: Wright's Traditional Coal Tar Soap 002629, 500 gram, Pack of 4
Review:
I procured a pack of these heading into the CV19 era as a backup, thinking that there would come a time when, bereft of all liquid soap, all fragrant latherings, we would be forced to turn native, to return to the scent of coal tar soap....

I had to turn to it sooner than I ever expected..... The increased washing with the Blue scented liquid soap did no favours to my delicate digits. Dryness and itchiness setting in irrespective of how much Scandinavian hand cream I applied twixt scrubbing.

I started on the Wright's and immediately knew the Right choice had been made...

I was catapulted back to childhood days....that smell...it lingers....and I remember

No more dryness, no more itchy prickly pinkies....just a dab of hand cream and life is good...

However......the department of infernal affairs, (she who must be listened to..)..despises the smell....but I've been allowed to keep my bar of Wright's in a sealed box, by the sink. ...for now...

Product: Hibiscrub Health Care, 500ml
Review:
Thankfully, I thought about this product as soon as the virus that we all want to be eradicated raised its head. Well, this was probably my best purchase for sanitising my hands. This gel is antiseptic and given it is used before conducting surgery and minor operations, I think it's effectiveness is unquestionable.

I am very thorough when washing my hands and usually rub the gel into my hands for around 3 minutes, with close attention to all areas and under the nails. However, the peace of mind afterwards is fantastic, as even though I take a sanitizer with me too, you feel "bulletproof" knowing this product has a residual effect for up to 6 hours!

The smell is pleasant and I have not had any allergic reaction despite having sensitive skin. However, this handwash is not cheap but you get what you pay for, so the peace of mind is worth every penny!!!

Review: I know the product has got a lot of good reviews which is why I decided to try it. I‚Äôve used Listerine for years but different ones mostly either citrus, original or mild mint. My mouth isn‚Äôt usually sensitive to things but I found this far too strong to such an extent it left me with a very sore mouth which even after stopping use is still sore especially y tongue and roof of my mouth. Product: Listerine Total Care Mouthwash, 600 ml
Review:
Although the taste of this mouthwash is great, I feel that it's too strong and harsh. My gums, lips and tongue always feel raw after using this and it often results in skin peeling off my inner lip.

It leaves my teeth clean and breath fresh but the side effects are not worth it. It may be as it has alcohol in it which is contributing to the dry mouth. I don't have a sensitive mouth or teeth so I am attributing this to the mouthwash.

I haven't experienced whitening at all since use.

Personally not for me.

Product: Seven Seas JointCare Active, With Glucosamine, Omega-3, Chondroitin, Vitamins C and D, Manganese, Zinc, Food Supplements, 30-Day Pack
Review: I have no issue with the seller of these capsules.My issues is with Seven Seas Seas itself,  2 days into the 4 days I started taking the capsules. I started to become very bloated, like I was 6 months pregnant and very very painful cramps for 48 hours. I realized the only thing that had changed in my diet was taking these capsules. So i looked at the list of ingredients, the 3rd ingredient is SORBITOL SYRUP.Which I then fine out can cause abdominal cramps,bloating,  dehydration and  diarrhoea to name just a few of the side effects of indigestion SORBITOL.Knowledge is power, if a person is unaware of the side effects of this ingredient it could greatly affect there health.

Product: Seven Seas JointCare Active, With Glucosamine, Omega-3, Chondroitin, Vitamins C and D, Manganese, Zinc, Food Supplements, 30-Day Pack
Review: I have a knee injury which hinders my ability to run long distance..... NOT ANY LONGER!! after 3-4 months of taking these tablets my knee no longer hurts and I do a 10k run 5 times a week without any issues... highly recommend if you have any injuries

Product: Seven Seas JointCare Active, With Glucosamine, Omega-3, Chondroitin, Vitamins C and D, Manganese, Zinc, Food Supplements, 30-Day Pack
Review: Both my parents who are in their 80s have been taking these for a number of years and they appear to have helped with joint aches etc. I have been taking them for the past few months and find they help me, although I wish they didn't have sorbitol in them as I have a minor intolerance of the substance. Overall, though a good product but watch the value for money between the 30 and 60 packs.

Product: Wright's Traditional Coal Tar Soap 002629, 500 gram, Pack of 4

May work for some but for bad Eczema I wouldn't recommend.Found a soap called Cetaphil, Seems to be working so far, It's expensive but it works. By I mean it works I mean it will not dry your skin, Not a cure. It will just allow you to wash your hands without a breakout, I'd recommend still sticking to your medication. Skin clear for 3 weeks.

Product: Wright's Traditional Coal Tar Soap 002629, 500 gram, Pack of 4
Review:
In the 1860's this soap was a by-product of the distillation of coal to make coke; the liquid was made into Wrights¬†antiseptic soap for the treatment of skin diseases.

These days the use of coal tar in non-prescription products has been banned, and so the Wrights traditional (or not so traditional) soap you can buy only has a coal tar fragrance.¬†

Still, it's a good old fashioned soap with the same smell, just without¬†the coal tar!

Product: Wright's Traditional Coal Tar Soap 002629, 500 gram, Pack of 4
Review:
I procured a pack of these heading into the CV19 era as a backup, thinking that there would come a time when, bereft of all liquid soap, all fragrant latherings, we would be forced to turn native, to return to the scent of coal tar soap....

I had to turn to it sooner than I ever expected..... The increased washing with the Blue scented liquid soap did no favours to my delicate digits. Dryness and itchiness setting in irrespective of how much Scandinavian hand cream I applied twixt scrubbing.

I started on the Wright's and immediately knew the Right choice had been made...

I was catapulted back to childhood days....that smell...it lingers....and I remember

No more dryness, no more itchy prickly pinkies....just a dab of hand cream and life is good...

However......the department of infernal affairs, (she who must be listened to..)..despises the smell....but I've been allowed to keep my bar of Wright's in a sealed box, by the sink. ...for now...

Product: NRS Healthcare M03792 Home Helper Trolley - STANDARD (Eligible for VAT relief in the UK)
Review: I bought this trolley after a total hip replacement.  Being at home on my own part of the day, and on two crutches, I would not have been able to take my lunch and cuppas from the kitchen to the lounge without this trolley.  The trolley is very sturdy and I like the fact that the handles slope toward you.  The trays are strong and wipe easily.  There are no brakes, which wasn't a problem for me, but I would say that this may be a safety issue for anyone who is very infirm and unsteady on their feet.  I have found the trolley so useful that I will continue to use it when I am fully fit!

Review: I purchased this to treat a type of itchy eczema on the back of my head which was inside my hairline. I have long hair and creams were difficult to apply and made a mess. I apply after washing my hair and leave to dry; it keeps the eczema under control. The eczema does come back as per a lot of eczema but it always quickly clears it. I've used it recently on a weird itchy rash on the back of my hand and it took the nasty redness and heat out of it overnight.Currently treating my husband's conjunctivitis with it and it appears to be working on that as well.I realise we sound like a right pair üòÜWe do use it on the pets and it helps wounds heal quickly. Completely cures hotspots on my friend's labradoodle in just 24 hours. Magic stuff!

Product: Leucillin Natural Antiseptic Spray | Antibacterial, Antifungal & Antiviral | for Dogs, Cats and All Animals | for Itchy Skin and All Skin Care Health | 500ml
Review: My Boy has terrible malassezia issues in his ears and feet (standard Tibetan Terrier issues) and would spend all day licking his feet, I've been using malaseb shampoo which is a ball ache to use as Archie hates the shower and having to shower him multiple times a week is a nightmare,I'm a veterinary Nurse and thankfully a colleague of mine recommended Leucillin as she had met the team at VetFest, I contacted leucilling directly through my practice and asked if it might help with malassezia problems and they wrote a very informative email back,In short it's fantastic, so easy to use I sprayed Archie's feet 3 times a day for about a week and now I spray maybe once every three days and the yeast cleared up perfectly and I can genuinely say Archie never licks his paws now!the fact you can spray on and leave is the best part I find, I genuinely couldn't say if the formula is that effective (seems to me like a clever dose of salt and chlorine is literally all it is) compared to a vet prescribed product like Malaseb, but the ease of use means I can do.it more often and that has made it more effective and I will certainly continue to use and buy it! High recommend

Product: Leucillin Natural Antiseptic Spray | Antibacterial, Antifungal & Antiviral | for Dogs, Cats and All Animals | for Itchy Skin and All Skin Care Health | 500ml
Review: Leucillin really works on animals AND on humans! I noticed two days ago my horse had a runny eyes due to the flies and she is prone to get conjunctivitis (last year the cream the vet gave me for this was very expensive). So I sprayed this a few times in her eyes and by the next day the running had stopped and the eye was clear again. It really doesn't sting your eyes (my mare didn't mind it one bit)  - I have used it in my own eyes as it is safe for humans too. My partner got an insect bite today which really stung but as soon as he sprayed this on it the itchiness disappeared and it has almost cleared up now (a few hours later). My friend's horse had a horse fly bite yesterday and I brought out this trusty purple spray - the area is fine now and there is no swelling. I also use it also on my gelding's feathers to ward off feather mites and summer itching. It has really helped and there is very little foot stomping now. So I highly recommend this very versatile and effective spray that will benefit you in so many ways :)

Product: Leucillin Natural Antiseptic Spray | Antibacterial, Antifungal & Antiviral | for Dogs, Cats and All Animals | for Itchy Skin and All Skin Care Health | 500ml
Review: I used this on my cats Hotspot when she had a flea bite reaction and she started itching the skin and fur off her tail. It was really bad but the spray did help! Now however she is averse to spray bottles so thought she was being reprimanded and purposefully irritated so she became rather depressed. Also after using this on my blisters IT STUNG LIKE HELL! so I don't know maybe it actually hurts alot! And Though her skin infection healed she would still lick at it before it could fully recover. Review: I tracked this down after reading an article about how hypochlorous acid (HOCl) was an effective disinfectant several orders of magnitude more powerful than hypochlorite (as in bleach). Bought it on basis of so many positive reviews cross-referenced with several scholarly articles. It is a chemical that our own cells produce in the immune reaction, although obviously in tiny volumes, and was used in WW1 on wards. Problem has been producing it in a stable form, it used to have to be generated on-site, but recent advances have come up with solutions with shelf-lives of a year or so.In anti SARS-CoV-2 sense we use it for misting items we‚Äôve brought back from the shops, for disinfecting surfaces, spraying down our outside gear etc. But we‚Äôve also found it seems to have given our cockatiel some relief from self-plucking of his shoulder feathers. Just like all the dog and cat-owners have said he doesn‚Äôt flinch or seem to experience any discomfort whatsoever and just seems to be calmer and more comfortable. We sprayed it on ourselves first to test, no sting, just a slight tang of swimming pool. Great product.

Product: GoGirl Planner and Organizer for Women ‚Äì Compact Size Weekly Planner, Goals Journal & Agenda to Improve Time Management, Productivity & Live Happier. Undated ‚Äì Start Anytime, Lasts 1 Year ‚Äì Rose Gold
Review:
I received this planner yesterday and was so eager to try it out, I opened it immediately! The color was great, it had 3 different color page placers, a spot to hold your pen, a little pocket in the very back that had stickers, in the front it has several pages for you to write down your goals and on each month page it has spots so that you can update your goals and the quality seemed pretty great.
Unfortunately this specific planner is not going to work for me. The dates had to be filled in by hand which isn't horrible except for the months where there are '6' weeks so to speak. There are only 5 weeks worth of blocks so some months didn't fit all the way. For me personally, I want my full months available instead of having to flip the page for the remainder of the month.
Also, I did not realize it, but there was no additional pages for "notes". Instead it has dotted pages in the back. For some that may be great but for me, I will not use it and prefer to have the note pages.
The last thing that I found wouldn't work for me was the size. This was a fail on my part as the listing gives you the dimensions of the planner, however, I didnt realize that the spaces to write in would be as small as they were. Again, that was a judgment fail on my part since this is a tablet sized planner. After having this is realized that I need a full (bigger) size option.
Before even receiving the planner I received a message from the seller thanking me for my purchase and stating that they have a 60 day money back guarantee if you dont absolutely love it and to please reach out with any issues. So I reached out and expressed my minor issues. I received a response very quickly offering a replacement (one that has the dates already filled in) or a full no hassle refund. Unfortunately I declined the replacement since it was only able to correct 1 of the 3 flaws. They issued a refund immediately after my decline and even told me not to worry about returning the original. The customer service with this company was phenomenal!!! Even though it did not work for me, I still give this product 5 stars.

Product: GoGirl Planner and Organizer for Women ‚Äì Compact Size Weekly Planner, Goals Journal & Agenda to Improve Time Management, Productivity & Live Happier. Undated ‚Äì Start Anytime, Lasts 1 Year ‚Äì Rose Gold
Review: After so many planners (electronic and paper) I found the Go-Girl. I love that it is blank and yet has some structure for me to build in. The planner lets you create your own input (not predetermined by a bunch of labeled areas) but also gives format that supports planning for months, weeks, and long-term goals. I have adapted this planner to my needs. It's awesome that it has a weekly view so I can see all my to-dos and my plans in one glance. The only caveat I would say to buyers here is be sure to click the size you want - I accidentally clicked the smaller size and had to re-order later. I like the larger option so I can fit more in. The larger one is still small enough to be easy to carry and fit in my purse. Totally recommend this planner.

Product: GoGirl Planner and Organizer for Women ‚Äì Compact Size Weekly Planner, Goals Journal & Agenda to Improve Time Management, Productivity & Live Happier. Undated ‚Äì Start Anytime, Lasts 1 Year ‚Äì Rose Gold
Review: I was pleasantly surprised with how much I like this planner! I have tried bullet journal style planning for a couple of years now, and I always fall behind because it takes a lot of time to draw out the pages for the upcoming week. I love how this planner has a monthly and a weekly spread, but they are blank so you can fill in the dates yourself (which is really helpful to me because there are some weeks I just don't think to plan, and I don't feel like I am wasting any paper since I can just use the next page, even if it's a couple weeks down the road.) I am happy that the second page of each week has a few helpful trackers, for the week's priorities, a to-do list, and a habit tracker, and below that, it has BULLET JOURNAL space on the lower half of the page. So I can put my own things down. At the back, there are quite a few pages of bullet journal space as well, so I have a perfect mix of being able to do big things in the BuJo pages, but not have to draw out a schedule from scratch each week. I also love that there are THREE bookmarks attached so you can keep one in each section of the planner.I will say, the one thing that I wish is that there were a couple different options to choose from with the layout of the weekly spread. I would personally like the dates to go across the top of the two page spread, rather on the first page, and then have the trackers and BuJo space underneath, also going across both pages.

Product: Leucillin Natural Antiseptic Spray | Antibacterial, Antifungal & Antiviral | for Dogs, Cats and All Animals | for Itchy Skin, Minor-wound Care and All Skin Care Health | 250ml
Review:
Grass cutting season has started again... which means allergy season for 2 of my Maltese.
Not even 6 hours after the grass being cut they had both started to scratch and chew their paws.

I have tried many many creams and spray over the years, including various (expensive) treatments from the vet and even the use of steroids for one of them as she had got so bad she was going bald with all her itching!

My male had managed to scratch a horrible sore onto his stomach area, I had tried treating it with another well- known dog anti itch brand for several days with no luck what so ever and figured it was going to have to be another vet trip before the cut turned into a full-blown wound and would get infected. I had seen this spray advertised several times but to be honest, I just assumed it would be the same as all the others I already have sitting in the cupboard which didn't work for us. However, when telling a friend I was going to have to take him back to the vet she recommended trying Leucillin Antiseptic Skin Care Spray and told me her vet uses it and that she had had great results too so decided it was worth a go.

Item arrived really quickly and spraying it onto the cut didn't seem to bother him at all. Within a day the sore had already started to look better. Even better my dog was no longer scratching at the area or trying to constantly lick it. Have used the spray for 3 days (twice a day although it does recommend 3 times) and today the area has completely healed and no longer red or sore. My other Maltese hasn't been as bad (so far) this year however she has been chewing at her paws a bit. I have given her feet a quick spray once a day and that alone seems to be enough to stop her biting and causing more harm.

Am truly amazed by how well it has worked, although have to say I'm a little annoyed I didn't purchase it sooner as I would have saved the dogs many summers of itching misery and myself many large vet bills!
